          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Final Exam Performance Risk Category",
          "(1) Risk of Dropping Out, (2) Risk of Scoring Lower in Final Exam, (3) Risk of Failing Final Exam",
          "32593 students",
          "22 course-edition pairs in OULAD",
          "LMS logs, Engagament Status, Course Instructor Behavior",
          "[Weekly Sequence of Behaviors, Demographics and Teaching Style of Course Instructor]",
          "End of Course",
          "The model is designed to do weekly evaluations of student potential success. The data is aggregated and given as argument to the ID2QN algorithm.\n\nAuthors extract engagement features from TSE and Yolov6",
          "PCT, MST-FaDe, Fuzzy-SVM, AISAR, ID2QN",
          "Unspecified",
          "{Accuracy: 0.97 - ID2QN, F1-score: 0.95 -ID2QN, Recall: 0.99 - ID2QN}",
          "Work combines the detection of learners at risk with recommendations. \n\nFor that, it integrates 3 main fields of study: AI, Federated Learning and Cloud Computing.\n\nAll reported results are for classification performance of early warning model (ID2QN). No empirical evaluation of the recommendation module (Att-CapsNet). Gains over baselines are very large but methodology for split/validation is unclear.\n",
          "- Poorly written with the assistance of a LLM. \n\n- Unclear source of emotional data \n\n- No Validation Method is mentioned\n\nNo Ablation Study\n\n- Only OULAD\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    }
