    {
      "id": "df2c55ef-e0d1-454a-a926-eb987be35ed2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The authors propose EFedCloud, an adaptive environment that automatically tracks student progress and makes personalized recommendations. The system makes a weekly evaluation of student engagement. This, along with other attributes are then given as input to a DRL early warining system that predicts performance of non-engaged students. \n\nAfter a prediction is made, the students are categorized based on expected performance on the final exam. Then, it takes all of these datapoints to make a personalized recommendation to the student on what contents to visit next, with sensitive data being encrypted using LWEA.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "df2c55ef-e0d1-454a-a926-eb987be35ed2",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
          "page_id": "20c5e80c-6952-4f17-b0aa-bc2302cfd1fe"
        },
        "created_time": "2024-08-06T16:49:00.000Z",
        "last_edited_time": "2024-08-06T16:54:00.000Z",
